m(t) = (pe^t + q)^n,
q = 1 âˆ’ p.
m(t) = E(e^{tY}) = \sum_{y=0}^n \binom{n}{y}(pe^t)^yq^{n-y}.
N
X \sim \text{Bin}(n,p)
X \stackrel{d}{=} \sum_{k=1}^n Y_k
Y_1,...,Y_k
M_{Y_1}(t)= 1-p+p\exp(t)
 \begin{align} M_X(t) &= E[e^{tX}]\\ &= E\left[ \exp\left(t \sum_{k=1}^n Y_k \right)\right] \\ &=  E\left[  \prod_{k=1}^n\exp\left(t  Y_k \right)\right] \\ &=   \prod_{k=1}^nE\left[\exp\left(t  Y_k \right)\right] \\ &= \prod_{k=1}^n (1-p+p\exp(t)) \\ &=(1-p+p\exp(t))^n \end{align} 
